'''Darkness into Light''' is an annual walking event and fundraiser held, primarily, across the [[Ireland|island of Ireland]].<ref name="IT2016">{{cite web |date=7 May 2016 |accessdate=10 May 2017 |url=https://www.irishtimes.com/news/ireland/irish-news/more-than-120-000-take-part-in-darkness-into-light-walk-1.2639587 |title=‘More than 120,000’ take part in Darkness into Light walk |first=Dean |last=Ruxton |work=[[Irish Times]]}}</ref> Participants meet before dawn (4.15am) on a particular Saturday in May and walk or run for 5km to meet the sunrise.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.irishtimes.com/news/social-affairs/thousands-take-part-in-darkness-into-light-walks-worldwide-1.2206691 |work=[[Irish Times]] |date=9 May 2015 |accessdate=10 May 2017 |title=Thousands take part in Darkness into Light walks worldwide |first=Sorcha |last=Pollak}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thejournal.ie/pieta-house-event-shows-light-at-end-of-darkness-439182-May2012/ |title=Pieta House event shows light at end of darkness |date=5 May 2012 |accessdate=10 May 2017 |work=TheJournal.ie}}</ref> Founded in 2009 by psychologist [[Joan Freeman (politician)|Joan Freeman]] as a fundraiser in the [[Phoenix Park]] for [[Pieta House]] suicide prevention and counselling, 400 attended the first event while the 2017 event was attended by an estimated 150,000<ref name="RTE14"/><ref name="BN2017"/> - 200,000<ref name="ITTaoiseach"/> participants at more than 150 locations.<ref name="BN2017">{{cite web |url=http://www.breakingnews.ie/ireland/here-are-some-of-the-images-from-the-darkness-into-light-event-788554.html |title=Here are some of the images from the Darkness into Light event |work=BreakingNews.ie |date=6 May 2017 |accessdate=10 May 2017}}</ref> Similar events occur in Australia and New Zealand, Asia and North America.<ref name="IT2016"/><ref name="RTE14">{{cite web |publisher=[[RTÉ News]] |url=https://www.rte.ie/news/2014/0510/616435-darkness-to-light-pieta-house/ |date=10 May 2014 |accessdate=10 May 2017 |title=Thousands take part in 'Darkness into Light' fundraising event}}</ref> The [[Taoiseach]] [[Enda Kenny]] attended an DIL event in [[Toronto]] in [[Canada]] during a state visit there in 2017.<ref name="ITTaoiseach">{{cite web |first=Michael |last=O'Regan |url=https://www.irishtimes.com/news/politics/oireachtas/taoiseach-had-neck-to-go-on-canadian-darkness-into-light-walk-says-senator-1.3077360 |title=Taoiseach had ‘neck’ to go on Canadian Darkness into Light walk, says Senator |date=9 May 2017 |accessdate=10 May 2017 |work=[[Irish Times]] }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.breakingnews.ie/ireland/pieta-house-founder-surprised-enda-kenny-had-the-neck-to-take-part-in-darkness-into-light-788960.html |work=BreakingNews.ie |date=9 May 2017 |accessdate=10 May 2017 |title=Pieta House founder surprised Enda Kenny had 'the neck' to take part in Darkness Into Light}}</ref>
