{{Infobox medical condition | name = High pressure injection injury | image = | alt = | caption = | pronounce = | synonym = | field = | DiseasesDB = | ICD10 = T70.4 | ICD9 = | ICDO = | OMIM = | MedlinePlus = | MeSH = | GeneReviewsNBK = | GeneReviewsName = | Orphanet = }} A '''grease gun injury''' or '''injection injury''' is an injury caused by high-pressure injection of [[oil]], [[petroleum|grease]], [[Unit injector|diesel fuel]], [[gasoline direct injection|gasoline]], solvents, water, or even air, into the body.<ref name="verhoeven">{{cite journal|last1=Verhoeven|first1=N|last2=Hierner|first2=R|title=High-pressure injection injury of the hand: an often underestimated trauma: case report with study of the literature.|journal=Strategies in trauma and limb reconstruction (Online)|date=April 2008|volume=3|issue=1|pages=27–33|pmid=18427921|pmc=2291478|doi=10.1007/s11751-008-0029-9}}</ref> The most common causes are accidents with [[grease gun (tool)|grease guns]], [[Spray painting|paint sprayers]], and [[pressure washer]]s, but working on diesel and gasoline engine fuel injection systems as well as pinhole leaks in pressurized hydraulic lines can also cause this injury. Additionally, there is at least one known case of deliberate self-injection with a grease gun.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Kalsi|first1=JS|last2=Arya|first2=M|last3=Peters|first3=J|last4=Minhas|first4=S|last5=Ralph|first5=DJ|title=Grease-gun injury to the penis.|journal=Journal of the Royal Society of Medicine|date=May 2002|volume=95|issue=5|pages=254|pmid=11983770|pmc=1279682|doi=10.1258/jrsm.95.5.254}}</ref>
Although the initial wound often seems minor, the unseen, internal damage can be severe. With [[hydraulic fluid]]s, paint, and detergents, these injuries are extremely serious as most hydraulic fluids and [[Solvent|organic solvents]] are highly toxic. Delay in surgical treatment often leads to amputations or death.<ref name="verhoeven" /> But even with pure water or air, these injuries cause [[compartment syndrome]] which leads to cell death if surgical intervention is delayed.
